{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1445424579,"nonce":"xMBqjl79uHNlOGiQJRCc3NMj474=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0OTg1MjUwNw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/345#issuecomment-149852507"},"message":"@erasche this is great! Where is the code. I'm wondering why we need a web-service at all, if we just want to map the packages to a URL.\n\nThe problem of archiving tarballs has two sides for me.\n1. provide a stable URL to the tarballs \n2. store the archives\n\nHere is how I would imaging a solution for problem 1:\n\n```\ncurl  https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bgruening/gsl/master/gsl.py | python - --package_id augustus_3_1\n```\n\nThis will download a package a ID `augustus_3_1`. The ID is unique and we can use it inside of `download_by_url` directly, if we implement something like https://github.com/bgruening/gsl/blob/master/gsl.py in Galaxy directly. We do not need to store the checksum inside of the tool_dependency as this script will take care of it. Not sure if github is happy with this usage, but essentially we do not need a server and can just collect and update all URLs in one place. But this makes it to a central point failure.\n\nThat said, for the second problem I think we need to get founding for a download store to actually store the tarballs somewhere. My idea was to ask the ELIXIR project and especially the [Sustainability Institute](http://www.sustainabilityinstitute.net/) for help.","files":null}]}